content: Met with the quant firm's team lead. They're excited about my AI project. It's not just a side hustle anymore; it's my ticket to a permanent role.
Got feedback on my blog draft. My mentor suggested I dive deeper into how tech shapes identity. Time to get introspective.
Just secured my first workshop on ethical AI. It's happening next month. The gears are turning.
The AI bot had its first real-world test. It made a small profit. Not bad for a beginner, right?
Explored a space tech startup pitch. Their sustainable approach to Mars colonization is intriguing. Might invest.
Wrote a piece on neural augmentation for the blog. The line between enhancement and ethics is thinner than I thought.
The quant firm offered me a full-time position. My AI bot impressed them. I guess I'm not just a cog in the machine anymore.
Had a coffee with a friend who's into urban transport. Autonomous vehicles could change everything. We brainstormed some ideas.
Fleshed out the AI ethics workshop. It's about time we had these conversations.
Started incorporating sustainable tech into my daily life. Solar-powered chargers, anyone?
My AI bot is now part of the firm's trading strategy. It's surreal seeing my code in action.
Wrote about the potential of multi-planetary resource management. The future is not just on Earth, it's everywhere.
Got an invitation to speak at a tech conference on quantum-resistant blockchain. The timing couldn't be better.
Sometimes, I wonder if all this tech progress is just some cosmic game. Like, what if we're all just characters in some grand simulation?
Planning my next blog post on how technology shapes identity. I'm not just coding; I'm telling my story through tech.
